{
  "id": "019ce580-dc30-7d33-90f6-51dd094f9465",
  "content": "# LinkedIn Post Writing Style — Em Dash Overuse\n\nRecurring issue: AI-generated LinkedIn post copy overuses em dashes (—). This has been flagged multiple times by the author.\n\n## Rule\n- Maximum 1 em dash per post, and only when it creates strong dramatic contrast (e.g. \"used to take an afternoon — Claude handled it in minutes\")\n- Default to periods, commas, colons, or semicolons instead\n- Em dashes feel punchy in isolation but become a crutch when overused — they make writing feel formulaic and AI-generated\n\n## Alternatives\n- \"workloads — embeddings and chat —\" → \"workloads: embeddings and chat.\"\n- \"sessions are independent — each gets\" → \"sessions are independent. Each gets\"\n- \"took an afternoon — Claude handled it\" → \"took an afternoon, but Claude handled it\" (or keep the dash if it's the only one)\n\n## Applies to\nAll LinkedIn post copy in `docs/marketing/linkedin/*/post.html`",
  "source_version": "mcp",
  "scope_id": "corvia",
  "workstream": "main",
